body:
When upgrading our code base to v5.024, we encountered the following error.
```
%Error: Internal Error: t/t_module_output_error.v:3:10: ../V3DfgPasses.cpp:314: Variable inlining should make this impossible
```
Running on Ubuntu 18.04.3 LTS. This can be reproduced using the test below.
```
// t_module_output_error_2.v
module t_module_output_error_2(input in, output out);
  assign out = in;
endmodule

// t_module_output_error.v
module t_module_output_error(input clk, output out);
  logic one = '1;
  t_module_output_error_2 dut_inst(.in(one), .out(out));
endmodule

// t_module_output_error.pl
#!/usr/bin/env perl
if (!$::Driver) { use FindBin; exec("$FindBin::Bin/bootstrap.pl", @ARGV, $0); die; }
# DESCRIPTION: Verilator: Verilog Test driver/expect definition
#
